This project's overall pipeline structure (prefilter → 1-D gate → blob
assembly → 2-D gate → centroid) was informed by study of cedar-detect
(github.com/smroid/cedar-detect, Apache-2.0 licensed). No cedar-detect
source code is retained in this branch — the detection algorithm here is
a textbook matched filter, independently implemented. The pipeline
architecture is acknowledged as inheriting from the same family of
designs.

The matched-filter detector is grounded in classical signal-detection
theory (North 1943, Turin 1960, Van Trees 1968).
